# Complete Go Best Practices Guide

## 1. Coding Style

### Formatting
```bash
# Auto format
go fmt ./...

# Stricter formatting
goimports -w .
```

### Naming Conventions
```go
// Package: lowercase, singular
package user

// Function: camelCase
func GetUserByID(id int) (*User, error)

// Variable: camelCase
var userCount int

// Constant: camelCase
const MaxRetries = 3

// Exported: starts with capital
type User struct {}

// Unexported: starts with lowercase
type user struct {}
```

## 2. Error Handling

### Basic Pattern
```go
// Always check errors
result, err := someFunction()
if err != nil {
    return nil, fmt.Errorf("someFunction failed: %w", err)
}

// Last return value is error
func DoSomething() (Result, error)

// Custom errors
var ErrNotFound = errors.New("not found")

type ValidationError struct {
    Field string
    Message string
}

func (e *ValidationError) Error() string {
    return fmt.Sprintf("%s: %s", e.Field, e.Message)
}
```

## 3. Concurrency

### Goroutines
```go
// Wait with WaitGroup
var wg sync.WaitGroup

for i := 0; i < 10; i++ {
    wg.Add(1)
    go func(i int) {
        defer wg.Done()
        // Process
    }(i)
}

wg.Wait()

// Cancel with Context
ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)
defer cancel()

go func() {
    select {
    case <-ctx.Done():
        fmt.Println("Cancelled")
        return
    case result := <-ch:
        fmt.Println(result)
    }
}()
```

## 4. Performance

### Memory Efficiency
```go
// Pre-allocate slice capacity
slice := make([]int, 0, 100)

// String concatenation with strings.Builder
var builder strings.Builder
for i := 0; i < 1000; i++ {
    builder.WriteString("test")
}
result := builder.String()

// Pointer vs Value
// Small structs: pass by value
type Point struct { X, Y int }
func Move(p Point) Point

// Large structs: pass by pointer
type LargeStruct struct { /* many fields */ }
func Process(p *LargeStruct) error
```

## 5. Testing

### Table-Driven Tests
```go
func TestAdd(t *testing.T) {
    tests := []struct {
        name string
        a, b int
        want int
    }{
        {"positive", 1, 2, 3},
        {"negative", -1, -2, -3},
        {"zero", 0, 0, 0},
    }

    for _, tt := range tests {
        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {
            got := Add(tt.a, tt.b)
            if got != tt.want {
                t.Errorf("Add(%d, %d) = %d; want %d",
                    tt.a, tt.b, got, tt.want)
            }
        })
    }
}
```

## 6. Security

```go
// Password hashing
import "golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt"

hash, _ := bcrypt.GenerateFromPassword([]byte(password), bcrypt.DefaultCost)
valid := bcrypt.CompareHashAndPassword(hash, []byte(password))

// SQL injection prevention
